### Description

I have a component that reads offsetWidth of div element.
```typescript
import { Component, effect, ElementRef, viewChild } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: '<div #div></div>',
  styles: `div { width: 250px; }`,
})
export class AppComponent {
  private _element = viewChild('div', { read: ElementRef });
  constructor() {
    effect(() =>
      console.log(
        'offsetWidth effect ' + this._element()?.nativeElement.offsetWidth
      )
    );
    setTimeout(
      () =>
        console.log(
          'offsetWidth timeout ' + this._element()?.nativeElement.offsetWidth
        ),
      100
    );
  }
}
```
If I run ng serve with hmr enabled: `ng serve --hmr=true` I get incorrect offsetWidth due to styles not being applied yet.
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/007bcc84-f4f5-4846-a99f-a3418b3fd039)
If I run ng serve with hmr disabled: `ng serve --hmr=false` I get correct result.
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/610e24a7-3d14-4c6a-b408-30e77529a8b6)

### Minimal Reproduction

1. Create new application
2. Paste code from above

